## Laptop strain: same desktop bundle as workstation, plus laptop firmware bits.
## NOTE: no tlp. On 24.04 tlp CONFLICTS with power-profiles-daemon (pulled in by
## ubuntu-desktop-minimal) -> "held broken packages", and it would fight the
## mode-switcher, which drives power via powerprofilesctl (power-profiles-daemon).
## So laptop power management = power-profiles-daemon + distro-modectl's governor
## control: the GNOME-integrated, conflict-free path.
ubuntu-desktop-minimal
flatpak
gnome-shell-extensions
gnome-tweaks
gamemode
mangohud
winetricks
fwupd
laptop-detect
## Intel-laptop essentials (first real flash target is an Intel ThinkPad X1
## Carbon). intel-media-va-driver-non-free = VAAPI HW video decode on Iris Xe/UHD
## (without it, 4K/H.265 playback falls back to CPU -> hot, loud, battery drain).
## thermald = Intel thermal daemon (prevents aggressive throttling on thin
## chassis; self-disables on non-Intel/AMD). fprintd + libpam-fprintd = the
## fingerprint-reader stack so GNOME Settings can actually enroll the X1's sensor.
intel-media-va-driver-non-free
thermald
fprintd
libpam-fprintd
